This paper focuses on transfer learning in visual reasoning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained models and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper introduces a new model for visual reasoning, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and reasoning, making it relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization capabilities of the new model, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) as robots need to be able to generalize to new environments and situations.
